<div class="mb-requirement-container">
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-13947">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> </span>
      <b>NOTE: </b>Check out the Digital Resource Guide for the Aviation merit
      badge
      <a
        href="https://www.scouting.org/skills/merit-badges/digital-resource-guides/aviation/?utm_source=mb&amp;utm_medium=requirements&amp;utm_campaign=aviation"
        target="_blank"
        >HERE</a
      >
      for detailed information and helpful resources to engage your learning and
      assist you along on your merit badge journey! The official merit badge
      pamphlets are now free and downloadable
      <a
        href="https://filestore.scouting.org/filestore/Merit_Badge_ReqandRes/Pamphlets/Aviation.pdf"
        target="_blank"
        >HERE</a
      >
      or can be purchased at the
      <a href="https://www.scoutshop.org/" target="_blank">Scout Shop!</a>
      Additional educational resources are available on our
      <a
        href="https://www.scouting.org/skills/merit-badges/counselor-information/"
        target="_blank"
        ><b>Counselor Information Page.</b></a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-12667">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 1. </span>
      <b>Aviation Basics and Mechanics of Flight.</b> Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12667 mb-requirement-id-12668">
        (a) Define "aircraft." Describe three kinds of aircraft today, and their
        typical uses. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/QvfVX2TXeb0" target="_blank"
          >Types of Aircraft (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/pI8u8fQmtIo" target="_blank"
          >Basics of How a Glider Works (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12667 mb-requirement-id-13845">
        (b) Provide a brief overview of the evolution of flight, and discuss
        three notable times in history important to aviation. <br /><i
          >Resources:</i
        >
        <a href="https://youtu.be/YDlk4Ky_ahs" target="_blank"
          >The Wright Brothers, First Successful Airplane (1903) (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/q_2AVyt9B_A" target="_blank"
          >The First Flight Around the World—U.S. Army Air Service (1924)
          (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/_R3fGL67mas" target="_blank"
          >First Solo Transatlantic Flight —Charles Lindbergh (1927) (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/y-itPeJOyzI" target="_blank"
          >First Solo Transatlantic Flight—Amelia Earhart (1932) (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/7O_iQ5LMGXI" target="_blank"
          >First Commercial Jet Airliner—de Havilland Comet (1949) (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/gH7MMJOOiUQ" target="_blank"
          >First Commercial Supersonic Flight—The Concorde (1969) (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/TunNolO9J4U" target="_blank"
          >First Flight Around the World Without Refueling—Rutan Model 86
          Voyager (1986) (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/WDp1DFih-po" target="_blank"
          >FAA Approves Unmanned Aerial Vehicles (UAV's AKA Drones) (2006)
          (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12667 mb-requirement-id-12669">
        (c) Explain the difference between a fixed wing and a rotary wing
        aircraft, and the benefits of each. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/Qju0JTn3PvI" target="_blank"
          >Airplane or Helicopter—Which Should You Choose? (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12667 mb-requirement-id-12670">
        (d) Explain the operation of piston, turbine, and jet engines. <br /><i
          >Resources:</i
        >
        <a href="https://youtu.be/5tN6eynMMNw" target="_blank"
          >The Internal Combustion Engine (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/kz5kv0RfeUc" target="_blank"
          >How a Turbine Engine Works (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/KjiUUJdPGX0" target="_blank"
          >See a Jet Engine in Action! (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12667 mb-requirement-id-12671">
        (e) Using a model aircraft, describe the four forces that act on an
        aircraft in flight. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/wFTHh-6jIT8?si=xxdao5Ldgl9Ll3S9"
          target="_blank"
          >How Do Planes Fly? (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12667 mb-requirement-id-12672">
        (f) Explain how an airfoil generates lift, specifically noting
        Bernoulli's principle. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/YrSUxgiwoFk" target="_blank"
          >Bernoulli's Principle: How Planes Fly (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12667 mb-requirement-id-12688">
        (g) Identify and describe the aerodynamic control surfaces on the
        aircraft of your choice, and explain how they operate to control its
        attitude and direction of flight. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/XxrdhJanotw" target="_blank"
          >Aircraft Control Surfaces Explained (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12667 mb-requirement-id-12689">
        (h) Explain the purposes and functions of the various instruments found
        in a typical single-engine aircraft: attitude indicator, heading
        indicator, altimeter, airspeed indicator, turn and bank indicator,
        vertical speed indicator, compass, navigation, communication, and engine
        performance indicators. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/NZn7Dd2jYFw" target="_blank"
          >Cessna Cockpit Tour (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/NLE9sDSRj-Y" target="_blank"
          >How To Control an Airplane: How Does a Pilot Control the Plane?
          (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-12673">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 2. </span>
      <b>Principles of Flight.</b> Do ONE of the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12673 mb-requirement-id-12674">
        (a) Build a model FPG-9. Get others in your troop or patrol to make
        their own model, then organize a competition to test the precision of
        flight and landing of the models. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a
          href="https://www.gocivilairpatrol.com/media/cms/AEX_MARC_Activity_2_AMA_FPG9_Glider_A8316FDFF99FD.pdf"
          target="_blank"
          >AMA FPG-9 Glider Instructions (PDF)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/zU1DaUwPUhQ" target="_blank"
          >AMA FPG-9 Glider (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12673 mb-requirement-id-12675">
        (b) Build a rubber-band driven balsa wood airplane. Fly the plane for 25
        feet in a straight line, with a smooth landing. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/rjuGw-oreyY" target="_blank"
          >Balsa Wood Plane (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12673 mb-requirement-id-12676">
        (c) Build (or obtain) a fuel-driven or battery-powered electric model
        aircraft or drone. Obtain The Recreational UAS Safety Test (TRUST)
        certification, and fly the aircraft with a successful take-off and
        landing. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a
          href="https://www.faa.gov/uas/recreational_flyers/knowledge_test_updates"
          target="_blank"
          >Learn (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://www.scouting.org/the-recreational-uas-safety-test/"
          target="_blank"
          >Take the Test (website)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-12680">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 3. </span>
      <b>Flight Operations.</b> Do TWO of the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12680 mb-requirement-id-12681">
        (a) Using a flight simulator software package, set a course and fly the
        headings you have established with a successful take-off and landing.
        <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://www.scouting.org/skills/merit-badges/digital-resource-guides/aviation/3-a/#elementor-action%3Aaction%3Dpopup%3Aopen%26settings%3DeyJpZCI6IjIzODg4NSIsInRvZ2dsZSI6ZmFsc2V9)"
          target="_blank"
          >Microsoft Flight Simulator (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12680 mb-requirement-id-12682">
        (b) Under supervision, perform a preflight inspection of an aircraft.
        <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/4cwKZ0Q_Xug" target="_blank"
          >How to Preflight a Cessna 172 (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12680 mb-requirement-id-12696">
        (c) Observe and/or participate in an aircraft maintenance activity.
        Describe the maintenance schedule and requirements for an aircraft of
        your choice.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12680 mb-requirement-id-12697">
        (d) Obtain and learn how to read an aeronautical chart. Measure a true
        course on the chart; correct it for magnetic variation, compass
        deviation, and wind drift to determine a navigational heading for an
        aircraft. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/4Z-yGYn4w-A" target="_blank"
          >How To Read an FAA Sectional Aeronautical Chart (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12680 mb-requirement-id-12698">
        (e) With your parent or guardian's permission, take a discovery flight
        in an aircraft. Record the date, place, type of aircraft, and duration
        of flight. Report on your impressions of the flight.
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-12683">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 4. </span>
      <b> Airport Operations.</b> Do ONE of the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12683 mb-requirement-id-12684">
        (a) Visit an airport. After the visit, report on how the facilities are
        used, how runways are numbered, and how runways are determined to be
        "active."
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12683 mb-requirement-id-12685">
        (b) Visit a Federal Aviation Administration facility: Airport Traffic
        Control Tower (ATCT), Terminal Radar Approach Control (TRACON), Air
        Route Traffic Control Center (ARTCC), or Flight Standards District
        Office (FSDO). Report on the operation and your impressions of the
        facility. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://www.faa.gov/aircraft/air_cert/locate_office"
          target="_blank"
          >FAA's Facility Locator (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12683 mb-requirement-id-12686">
        (c) Visit a military aviation facility. Learn how that facility supports
        defense and/or civilian activities. Report on the operation and your
        impressions of the facility. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://installations.militaryonesource.mil/" target="_blank"
          >Identify a Nearby Military Aviation Facility (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12683 mb-requirement-id-12695">
        (d) Visit an aviation museum or attend an air show. Report on your
        impressions of the museum or show, and what you learned from the
        experience. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://affiliations.si.edu/" target="_blank"
          >Smithsonian Affiliations (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://www.airshowcenter.com/" target="_blank"
          >Air Shows (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://www.milavia.net/airshows/" target="_blank"
          >Miltary Air Shows (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://www.eaa.org/eaa/events" target="_blank"
          >Recreational Aviation Events (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://whichmuseum.com/place/united-states-2682?q=aviation"
          target="_blank"
          >Find a Museum (website)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-12687">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 5. </span>
      <b>Personal &amp; Professional Aviation Opportunities.</b> Do the
      following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12687 mb-requirement-id-12690">
        (a) Explain the following: the student pilot, the recreational pilot,
        the remote pilot, and the private pilot certificates.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12687 mb-requirement-id-12691">
        (b) Describe the benefits of the instrument rating. <br /><i
          >Resources:</i
        >
        <a href="https://youtu.be/pDciG07bauE" target="_blank"
          >How To Use Flight Instruments When Flying an Airplane (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/ZbxtvLj8CmA" target="_blank"
          >What Is Instrument Flight Rules (IFR)? (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/Nuzjui3toOA" target="_blank"
          >Instrument Rating | Tips, Challenges &amp; Benefits (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/O3PJd893M8o" target="_blank"
          >Your First Instrument Pilot's Lesson (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12687 mb-requirement-id-12692">
        (c) Explain the following: the commercial pilot certificate, the airline
        transport pilot certificate, and certified flight instructor (CFI).
        <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/qMlfpncS7Mk&amp;t=211" target="_blank"
          >Pilot Licenses Explained (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/ELv4oUNa-C4" target="_blank"
          >Certified Flight Instructor (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12687 mb-requirement-id-12693">
        (d) Identify an Aviation Exploring Post and/or Civil Air Patrol facility
        in your area. Learn about their activities and membership requirements.
        <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/zH4Nq6f2SDA" target="_blank"
          >Aviation Exploring Post Visiting Denton TX Airport (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://www.exploring.org/aviation/" target="_blank"
          >Aviation Exploring Posts (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/QHAoogkb6ts" target="_blank"
          >Gallatin Cap Visiting Montana (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://www.gocivilairpatrol.com/" target="_blank"
          >Find a Local CAP Squadron: (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12687 mb-requirement-id-12694">
        (e) Identify three career opportunities that would use skills and
        knowledge in aviation. Pick one and research the training, education,
        certification requirements, experience, and expenses associated with
        entering the field. Research the prospects for employment, starting
        salary, advancement opportunities and career goals associated with this
        career. Discuss what you learned with your counselor and whether you
        might be interested in this career. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/AQ75DC4WcS8" target="_blank"
          >Careers in Aviation (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/bnxcib-8S4s" target="_blank"
          >Aerospace Engineer Careers (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/KP15W-uTp2c" target="_blank"
          >Career as a Flight Dispatcher (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/x5WrHPtpzk8" target="_blank"
          >How To Become a Helicopter Pilot (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/TCThd0Vr0cQ" target="_blank"
          >Career as a Aircraft Maintenance Technician (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/GNN1gogcHdM" target="_blank"
          >5 Qualities To Be a Good Air Traffic Controller (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/S6a3XVIMnHE" target="_blank"
          >Career as a Flight Attendant (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/SCrPtl9R1jQ" target="_blank"
          >Unseen Airport Jobs You Won't Believe Exist! | Inside Hidden Roles
          That Keep Airports Running (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://www.bls.gov/ooh/Transportation-and-Material-Moving/Airline-and-commercial-pilots.htm"
          target="_blank"
          >Airline and Commercial Pilots Occupational Outlook (website)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
</div>
